<p>
  A leader in philanthropy in Arizona, The Bob & Renee Parsons Foundation needed a refresh for their existing website. Their original site was mostly a stream of news posts and did not provide much information on the organization, their story, or the grants they've provided. Our team at BIG YAM created a site that would not only maintain all of their existing content, but also tell the stories of the organization and those they've helped.
</p>

<p>
  This was project was created during my time at BIG YAM, The Parsons Agency. As the lead front-end developer, my contributions included:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    Collaborating with designers to code static HTML, CSS, and JavaScript based on their designs in Adobe Photoshop
  </li>
  
  <li>Building a custom WordPress theme and integrating templates with the CMS</li>
  
  <li>
    Leveraging custom post types in WordPress to extend the site's capabilities beyond blog posts and single pages
  </li>
  
  <li>
    Ensuring the new implementation properly accounted for hundreds of existing blog posts that would be ported over
  </li>
  
  <li>
    Designing and building out interactions for the grant eligibility flow, with a focus on simplicity
  </li>
  
  <li>
    Creating a responsive timeline of events to highlight significant dates across the Foundation's history
  </li>
  
  <li>Embedding a live Twitter feed</li>
  
  <li>Building custom HTML email templates and testing across a number of email clients</li>
</ul>

